 to Paris — to bring Yoplait to America","body":"In 1972 Bennet moved his family to Paris for a year of intensive immersion in the yogurt business, then used his Michigan dairy company to develop Yoplait USA, introducing it to the American market in 1974. He sold both companies to General Mills in 1975."},{"number":2,"category":"character","header":"Amherst's most alive alumnus — \"a rage to live\"","body":"His Amherst classmate wrote that Bennet had \"a presence I can only describe as 'a rage to live'... a force that transformed each setting, venue or place.\" He danced, competed, built businesses and pioneered platform tennis across the Midwest — \"his glass was always much more than half full.\""}],"sources":[{"label":"Wikipedia — William S. Bennet II","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/William_S._Bennet_II"}],"tags":["businessman"],"institutions":[{"institution_id":"INST018"}],"landmarks":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"artworks":[],"research_tags":[],"cross_connections":[],"quotes":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"statues":[],"bio":{"first_name":"William","middle_name":"S","last_name":"Bennet","married_names":[],"suffix":"II","nickname":"Billo","display_name":"William S Bennet II"},"military_service":[],"slug":"william-bennet-ii-1934"},"I00189":{"id":"I00189","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":false,"gender":"female","birth":{"year":1913,"month":5,"day":21,"city":"Manchester","county":"Hartford","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"baptism":{},"death":{"year":1940,"month":12,"day":10,"state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM025","plot_notes":"Cedar Hill Cemetery Hartford CT. FindAGrave confirms."},"residence":{"city":"Hartford","state":"Connecticut","country":"United States"},"classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_thomas_spouse":false,"is_talcott_spouse":false,"include_in_path_calculation":false,"descent_paths_to_thomas":0,"descent_f